# Why I'm doing this  (Brain Unloader)
#
# Copy this file to ~/.config/bscp-tools/motivation.md OR ./motivation.md
# and edit it with YOUR reasons. The launcher reads it and:
#   - Shows ONE random quote at startup (between banner and theme picker).
#   - Shows another one when the rule tracker says you're stuck.
#   - Lets you view the full file via the `motivation` command in the menu.
#
# Rules for the parser:
#   - Lines starting with `#` are comments (ignored).
#   - Lines starting with `##` are SECTION HEADERS (rendered but not quoted).
#   - Blank lines separate quotes; a "quote" is one or more consecutive
#     non-empty non-comment non-header lines.
#   - Lines starting with `-` are bullet items - parsed as separate quotes.
#
# Why this works: externalizing your motivation means the system reminds
# you when you're flagging. It's harder to get stuck on a single tool
# for 30 minutes when a quiet line at the top of the screen says
# "every minute on this counts toward your $X-an-hour job offer."

